==Finnish==
===Verb===

(profane) vituttaa

The vord ''vituttaa'' is one of a few Finnish verbs that in their basic form already describe an on-going thing, and can include the person experiencing the thing. ''Vituttaa'' means roughly "is deeply annoyed" (literally "it cunts"), and if no other person is indicated, in most cases it applies to the user of the word. 

The on-going status of annoyment is called [[vitutus]].

Derived from [[vittu]].

Some females may like to use the word ''[[kyrpii]]'' instead.

===Examples===

''Mua vituttaa'' means literally "I'm deeply annoyed". 

A Finn can go and meet a friend, and just say the one word, ''vituttaa'', to communicate their annoyment.

===Words with similar properties===

''[[panettaa]]'' "is craving to fuck" derived from ''[[panna]]'' "to fuck"

''hirvittää'' "is horrified". Derived from ''hirveä'' "horrible".

